snippet.textDisplay:
S-240, a bill that targets human organ trafficking, was unanimously passed on the evening of April 30 in the Canadian House of Commons. It was introduced by the Senate and was already approved by the Committee on Foreign Affairs and International Trade (AEFA) prior to voting in the House of Commons.

The Act amends the Criminal Code and the Immigration and Refugee Protection Act. The first is that unauthorized overseas organ transplant would be treated as criminal activities. The second is that those involved in organ trafficking will not be granted immigration or refugee status.
